# CSS and Styling Conventions

## CSS Variables for Theming

Use CSS custom properties for all themeable values:

```css
:root {
  /* Colors */
  --tree-select-bg: #fff;
  --tree-select-border: #d9d9d9;
  --tree-select-border-hover: #40a9ff;
  --tree-select-primary-color: #1890ff;

  /* Sizes */
  --tree-select-height-middle: 32px;
  --tree-select-border-radius: 6px;
  --tree-select-padding-horizontal: 11px;

  /* Transitions */
  --tree-select-transition: all 0.2s ease;
}
```

## Class Naming (BEM-like)

- Block: `.tree-select`
- Element: `.tree-select-selector`, `.tree-select-dropdown`
- Modifier: `.tree-select-selector-focused`, `.tree-select-node-disabled`
- State: `.tree-select-node-selected`, `.tree-select-dropdown-footer`

## Component Structure

- Main component CSS in same directory as component
- Import CSS in component file: `import './Component.css'`
- Responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Use `clsx` for conditional class names

## Styling Patterns

```tsx
// Conditional classes
className={clsx('tree-select-node', {
  'tree-select-node-selected': isSelected,
  'tree-select-node-disabled': disabled,
})}

// Inline styles for dynamic values
style={{
  transform: isSelected ? 'scale(1.02)' : 'scale(1)',
  transition: 'all 0.3s ease',
}}
```

## Performance Considerations

- Use `appearance: none` to remove default browser styles
- Prefer transforms over changing layout properties
- Use `will-change` for animations
- Leverage CSS containment where appropriate
